"title": "4281: stars",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4281",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Heavenly luminaries other than the sun and moon, often worshipped as gods by pagan nations. Scripture stresses that the stars were created by God, and are subject to him. Stars are often treated as symbols of the generosity of God, and his faithfulness to his promises.</p>\n<h2>The relationship between God and the stars</h2>\n<h3>God is the creator</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:16\">GEN 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:6\">NEH 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:7-Ps136:9\">PSA 136:7–136:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps148:3-Ps148:6\">PSA 148:3–148:6</a></p>\n<h3>The stars demonstrate the power of their maker</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:26\">ISA 40:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:7-Job9:9\">JOB 9:7–9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:31-Job38:33\">JOB 38:31–38:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:4-Ps147:5\">PSA 147:4–147:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:11-Isa45:12\">ISA 45:11–45:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:8\">AMO 5:8</a></p>\n<h2>Worship of the stars</h2>\n<h3>Prohibited by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:19\">DEU 4:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:3\">DEU 17:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:4-2Kgs23:5\">2KI 23:4–23:5</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment of star worshippers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:2\">JER 8:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:12-Jer19:13\">JER 19:12–19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:25-Amos5:27\">AMO 5:25–5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:4-Zeph1:5\">ZEP 1:4–1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:42-Acts7:43\">ACT 7:42–7:43</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of star worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:16\">2KI 17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:3-2Kgs21:5\">2KI 21:3–21:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:5\">2CH 33:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:11\">ACT 28:11</a></p>\n<h2>Reading the stars</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:13\">ISA 47:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:2-Dan2:5\">DAN 2:2–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:7\">DAN 4:7</a></p>\n<h2>Signs in the stars</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:4\">ISA 34:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:7-Ezek32:8\">EZK 32:7–32:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:13\">REV 6:13</a></p>\n<h2>The star of Bethlehem</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:9-Matt2:10\">MAT 2:9–2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:2\">MAT 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:7\">MAT 2:7</a></p>\n<h2>The stars illustrating God's promise to Abraham</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:5\">GEN 15:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:17\">GEN 22:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:22\">DEU 10:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:23\">1CH 27:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:23\">NEH 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:22\">JER 33:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:12\">HEB 11:12</a></p>\n<h2>Metaphorical references to the stars</h2>\n<h3>A coming ruler</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:17\">NUM 24:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The morning star</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:12-Isa14:13\">ISA 14:12–14:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:19\">2PE 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:28\">REV 2:28</a></p>\n<h3>Wandering stars</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:13\">JUD 1:13</a></p>\n<h3>Stars representing angels</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:16\">REV 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:20\">REV 1:20</a></p>\n<h3>God's people shining like stars</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:15\">PHP 2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:3\">DAN 12:3</a></p>",
